   <conbody>
      <div class="- topic/div ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">A system might be in bypass operation because:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li platform="PxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">The power supply to the rectifier is not secure
and the batteries are unavailable, discharged or out of tolerance.</p>
               </li>
               <li platform="WxW" class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">The power supply to the inverter is unavailable.</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">The system was manually switched to bypass operation from the
display panel without interruption. See chapter <xref href="How_to_Switch_From_Normal_Operation_to_Bypass_Operation_CPT_0000337781.dita"
                           scope="local"
                           type="concept"
                           class="- topic/xref "/>.</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
            <note class="- topic/note ">Bypass operation is also called static bypass because the
bypass is supplied over the static switch.</note>
         </p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">A switch to
bypass operation without interruption is only possible if the bypass
mains is available and within the tolerance range.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">The system
can be configured to switch over to bypass operation even if the inverter
is not synchronized to the bypass mains. However, this will result
in a 10â€“20 ms interruption to the output.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">If the bypass
mains becomes unavailable in bypass operation, the system will try
to switch over to normal operation<ph platform="PxW" class="- topic/ph "> or battery operation</ph>.</p>
         <p class="- topic/p ">
            <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">For systems with manual bypass switches: </b>When the
load is supplied over the static switch EN in bypass operation, the
manual bypass switch is in <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Auto</b> position.</p>
